----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model defines actor-permission-resource-interface structure for automated queue reorder requirement
-- Summary 2: Safety assertions check authorization, access control, and well-formedness
-- Summary 3: Acceptance criterion reachability predicate defined
-- Summary 4: Edge-case assertions model concurrency and reordering constraints
-- Assumption 1: Queue_Management_System is an Interface, not an Actor; initiator role is abstract Actor
-- Assumption 2: Write permission is sufficient for queue modifications
-- Assumption 3: Post1 represents the ordered queue state
-- Assumption 4: Channel count restricted between 1 and 2 due to conflicting NFR facts
-- Open issue 1: Conflicting NFR facts: nfr_fact_min_channel_latency (<=2) and nfr_fact_redundant_availability (>=2) together force #channel=2, which may be intended but is not documented
-- Open issue 2: nfr_assert_maintainability_no_cycle contradicts owner_always_accessible fact, causing automated check to always fail
-- Open issue 3: Queue_Management_System is typed as Interface but used as an initiator in predicates (type mismatch; cannot be set equal to Actor)
-- Open issue 4: Edge case assertions ec_safe_1, ec_safe_2, ec_safe_3 may be vacuously true or oversimplified due to lack of temporal ordering (not Alloy 6 temporal logic)


